node.text:
Republicans are here demanding unanimous consent (a procedural mechanism) for a bill to be immediately brought to the floor. This bill would require this administration to give us accountability of how many Americans are left behind, a plan to get them out, a plan to get our equipment, and demand that we do NOT recognize the Taliban as a legitimate government. 

We will see if Pelosi will allow it. Unfortunately we don’t expect she will.

node.text:
More and more keeps coming out about the unbelievable decisions that led up to this. 

Biden and his national security team have repeatedly tried to blame the military for this. Here’s the truth: Biden gave very clear direction that our mission would be (1) keep the Embassy and (2) withdraw ALL troops. Note that the mission for Biden was never to “evacuate citizens and allies”. This meant that the military could not possibly keep Bagram airfield, and could not secure Kabul either. That’s why this played out the way it has, because of the very first decision Biden made: get ALL troops out.
